radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is markedly abnormal with wall edema and mild adjacent fat stranding, measuring 10-12 mm with appendicoliths. No pneumonia, pleural effusion, bowel obstruction, or free fluid in the abdomen. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, kidneys, pancreas, and other abdominal organs appear normal. Few prominent reactive lymph nodes in the mesentery. A small amount of free fluid noted in the pelvis.
